      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:MNOVH2014">Nakanishi and von Hinüber 2014</ref>. It is in the series of inscriptions on railing uprights (pāyakas).</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  therasa aya <persName key="pers:Kan-Ṛṣirakṣita"><supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>sirakhitasa</persName> a<unclear>tevā</unclear>siniya
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  bhikhuniya <persName key="pers:Kan-Nāgukā">nāguyāya</persName> deyadhama
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>The pious gift of the nun <persName key="pers:Kan-Nāgukā">Nāguyā</persName> (Nāgukā), the pupil of the venerable Elder <persName key="pers:Kan-Ṛṣirakṣita">Isirakkhita</persName> (Ṛṣirakṣita).</p>
